    &lt;Title&gt;Endoscopy depr&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Was referred for endoscopy from Chest clinic was told my appointment was going to be 13:30 but wait for appointment letter. I explained I was on my own and had to pick up my child up from Windermere. Was told don’t worry you’ll be our first appointment. The appointment letter didn’t come through so had to confirm my appointment . Was then told my appointment was 14:15. I explained that I couldn’t wait for 4 hours as stated, they said no problem. I would be first in. . Got to Endoscopy dept. Was ignored by the receptionist for several moments before she final decided to acknowledge me and finally open her glass window. Sat for an hour and a quarter. Everyone came  in &amp;amp; out before us. I explained to the  senior nurse that I had to go and pick my son up from Windermere  school. I don’t have  any support . He came back and said that they were half way through the procedure and would be another  10-15 mins . I explained I had to get back and couldn’t wait much longer. I ended up having to choose between trying to get my health sorted on my child’s welfare.  I had to choose my child’s welfare. It’s ok saying that missed appointments cost the NHS money. But the Royal Preston Hospital doesn’t seem to work to timings. This isn’t the first time. At the chest clinic my appointment was 9:30 am to see the specialist. Still at 13::30 I hadn’t seen him so I was supposed to see him after I had my endoscopy. Needles to say  it was a waste of both of our times!!!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
